# Global StrongRule (Encoding Safety)

Always apply `Docs/StrongRule/incodingRule.js` policy.

Mandatory:
- Use `apply_patch` for code/text edits whenever possible.
- Avoid full-file rewrite patterns for text/code files.
- Verify UTF-8 safety after edits when content includes Korean text.

Forbidden write patterns for code/text edits:
- `Get-Content ... -Raw` followed by any full rewrite command
- `[System.IO.File]::WriteAllText(...)`
- `Set-Content`, `Out-File`, `Add-Content`
- redirect writes: `>`, `>>`
- pipeline redirect writes: `| tee`, `| out-file`, `| set-content`

Validation checklist:
1. Minimal line-level patch
2. No dangerous write command patterns
3. Inspect `git diff --word-diff` for corruption
4. Run available project validation/build step
